697
00:57:25,275 --> 00:57:27,845
裂缝再大一点 这满载物资的雪橇
Any wider and the fully laden sledge

698
00:57:27,845 --> 00:57:28,875
就会直沉海底
would sink to the bottom,

699
00:57:28,875 --> 00:57:30,915
且会一并拖下拉车的狗
dragging the dogs under.

700
00:57:33,955 --> 00:57:36,195
有条狗被困在雪橇下了
There's a dog trapped under the sledge

701
00:57:36,195 --> 00:57:40,955
但它却奇迹般地没有受伤
but, miraculously, even this one emerges unharmed.

702
00:57:42,915 --> 00:57:45,485
道格和摄制组其他人看到这幕
Doug and the rest of crew spot the problem

703
00:57:45,485 --> 00:57:47,185
便避开了那条道
and find a better route home.

704
00:57:50,275 --> 00:57:53,085
在冰层重新变得足够安全
It was another week before the ice was safe enough

705
00:57:53,085 --> 00:57:56,255
能拍摄捕鲸之前  他们又等了一周
for the crew to film the full narwhal hunt sequence.

706
00:57:57,875 --> 00:58:00,315
在这里  生存与否全凭对环境的了解
This shoot, more than any other,

707
00:58:00,315 --> 00:58:03,435
与其他拍摄过程相比  这次经历
highlights the importance of the complete trust

708
00:58:03,435 --> 00:58:07,155
尤其证明了《人类星球》摄制组
between the Human Planet crew and the local Inuit,

709
00:58:07,155 --> 00:58:12,075
与因纽特人间的互相信任  至关重要
in a place where knowing your environment is the key to survival.

